item.title: Nova Scotia Shooting Rampage Kills at Least 16
item.description: Sixteen people were dead after a shooting rampage in a rural part of the Canadian province of Nova Scotia, and a suspect was killed in a confrontation with police.

item.title: Governments Face Pressure to Ease Lockdowns
item.description: Coronavirus infections topped 2.4 million world-wide as the pandemic showed signs of easing in some countries and U.S. states, ramping up pressure to re-evaluate lockdowns.

item.title: Hong Kong Arrests Spark Anger From Movement That Has Left the Streets
item.description: The arrest of pro-democracy figures in Hong Kong has stirred anger in a protest movement that has stayed off the streets during the coronavirus pandemic and spurred calls to restart demonstrations this summer.

item.title: Mexican Mogul Resists Coronavirus Restrictions
item.description: As Covid-19 cases and deaths mount across Mexico, the country’s second richest businessman is publicly defying health recommendations meant to prevent the spread of the new coronavirus, sparking a confrontation with the government.

item.title: Afghan President's Palace Struck by Coronavirus
item.description: The coronavirus pandemic reached the presidential palace in Afghanistan’s capital, where at least 20 people working for President Ashraf Ghani have tested positive

item.title: Europe Slowly Emerges From Lockdown
item.description: For a look at how hard it is to press “play” on a Western economy still battling the new coronavirus, turn to Europe, which is freeing its shops and small businesses in stages, easing a continentwide lockdown that has kept nearly half a billion people at home.
